# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: StoryBeginnings | Scene: TheMorningAfterKate
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah woke first, finding Kate still asleep next to her, fully naked."
    new "Sarah woke first, finding Kate still asleep next to her, fully naked."

    old "In the early morning light, she observed Kate's body. It's curves, her firm stomach, muscular arms. A soldier's body, she realized."
    new "In the early morning light, she observed Kate's body. It's curves, her firm stomach, muscular arms. A soldier's body, she realized."

    old "She felt as if she was discovering Kate's body in ways she hadn't the night before."
    new "She felt as if she was discovering Kate's body in ways she hadn't the night before."

    old "As if realizing she was being observed, Kate began to stir."
    new "As if realizing she was being observed, Kate began to stir."

    old "Kate rolled over, her hair disheveled, and looked at Sarah."
    new "Kate rolled over, her hair disheveled, and looked at Sarah."

    old "Like what you see?"
    new "Like what you see?"

    old "Sarah, feeling caught out, looks away."
    new "Sarah, feeling caught out, looks away."

    old "It's a little late to start pretending to be modest now, Sarah."
    new "It's a little late to start pretending to be modest now, Sarah."

    old "Sarah could feel the blood flow to her head."
    new "Sarah could feel the blood flow to her head."

    old "There she went again, Sarah thought. Pushing her buttons."
    new "There she went again, Sarah thought. Pushing her buttons."

    old "Do you enjoy teasing me like that?"
    new "Do you enjoy teasing me like that?"

    old "Kate laughed."
    new "Kate laughed."

    old "Yeah, a little."
    new "Yeah, a little."

    old "You're insufferable."
    new "You're insufferable."

    old "Kate reached over, her hand under the blankets, placing it on Sarah's hips."
    new "Kate reached over, her hand under the blankets, placing it on Sarah's hips."

    old "Oh, I'm so sorry."
    new "Oh, I'm so sorry."

    old "Kate's voice wasn't serious at all."
    new "Kate's voice wasn't serious at all."

    old "I hope you can find it in your power to forgive me, your Royalty."
    new "I hope you can find it in your power to forgive me, your Royalty."

    old "Kate's hands began to slide down Sarah's sides, slowly going lower."
    new "Kate's hands began to slide down Sarah's sides, slowly going lower."

    old "Or maybe I need to work to earn your forgiveness."
    new "Or maybe I need to work to earn your forgiveness."

    old "For a moment, Sarah imagined letting Kate continue. To let get take her as she had last night."
    new "For a moment, Sarah imagined letting Kate continue. To let get take her as she had last night."

    old "Part of her wanted to. Shut the doors to her room and just stay here with Kate all day."
    new "Part of her wanted to. Shut the doors to her room and just stay here with Kate all day."

    old "But, right before the edge, Sarah's senses returned to her."
    new "But, right before the edge, Sarah's senses returned to her."

    old "Today was going to be busy. The council meeting would start before long, and she would have to be ready."
    new "Today was going to be busy. The council meeting would start before long, and she would have to be ready."

    old "Not to mention, Sarah didn't want anyone to find her and Kate in bed like this. That would raise far too many problems."
    new "Not to mention, Sarah didn't want anyone to find her and Kate in bed like this. That would raise far too many problems."

    old "Sarah grabbed Kate's wrist and pulled her hands away."
    new "Sarah grabbed Kate's wrist and pulled her hands away."

    old "Denying herself what she wanted pained her more than she thought."
    new "Denying herself what she wanted pained her more than she thought."

    old "I'm sorry Kate, but there is a council meeting, and I need to attend."
    new "I'm sorry Kate, but there is a council meeting, and I need to attend."

    old "Kate gave an exasperated sigh."
    new "Kate gave an exasperated sigh."

    old "Fine, but I'm not done with you yet."
    new "Fine, but I'm not done with you yet."

    old "Kate rolled out of the bed and began crawling across the floor, collecting her clothes."
    new "Kate rolled out of the bed and began crawling across the floor, collecting her clothes."

    old "Sitting up in bed, watching Kate scramble around, Sarah wondered if Kate was taking her time on purpose."
    new "Sitting up in bed, watching Kate scramble around, Sarah wondered if Kate was taking her time on purpose."

    old "Once Kate had finally collected her clothes, she began putting them on, slowly, making sure Sarah watched her."
    new "Once Kate had finally collected her clothes, she began putting them on, slowly, making sure Sarah watched her."

    old "Sarah, for her part, found it impossible to look away from Kate."
    new "Sarah, for her part, found it impossible to look away from Kate."

    old "Kate finished getting dressed, but suddenly climbed back onto the bed, pinning Sarah down again as she had done last night."
    new "Kate finished getting dressed, but suddenly climbed back onto the bed, pinning Sarah down again as she had done last night."

    old "She grabbed the back of Sarah's head and pulled her close. Kate began to kiss Sarah, forcing her tongue into Sarah's mouth."
    new "She grabbed the back of Sarah's head and pulled her close. Kate began to kiss Sarah, forcing her tongue into Sarah's mouth."

    old "Sarah did not resist."
    new "Sarah did not resist."

    old "Just as Sarah could feel her resolve fading, Kate jumped back off the bed, leaving the princess unsatisfied."
    new "Just as Sarah could feel her resolve fading, Kate jumped back off the bed, leaving the princess unsatisfied."

    old "Saying nothing else, Kate made a quick exit, stealing only one last glance of Sarah, before closing the door to her bedroom, exiting into the hallway."
    new "Saying nothing else, Kate made a quick exit, stealing only one last glance of Sarah, before closing the door to her bedroom, exiting into the hallway."

    old "The room was once again, empty."
    new "The room was once again, empty."

    old "Sarah began trying to process what had happend last night. She couldn't have ever imagined letting Kate do what she did to her...and yet, last night she had offered no resistance at all."
    new "Sarah began trying to process what had happend last night. She couldn't have ever imagined letting Kate do what she did to her...and yet, last night she had offered no resistance at all."

    old "Images of the night before began to flood Sarah's mind."
    new "Images of the night before began to flood Sarah's mind."

    old "She shook her head, trying to clear her thoughts."
    new "She shook her head, trying to clear her thoughts."

    old "There was work to be done. Every day, more and more people came to her and Thomas. The requests were endless."
    new "There was work to be done. Every day, more and more people came to her and Thomas. The requests were endless."

    old "With her father's funeral now behind them, the deluge of work would only increase."
    new "With her father's funeral now behind them, the deluge of work would only increase."

    old "Sarah came to realize just how much her Father had protected herself and Thomas from the reality of ruling a nation."
    new "Sarah came to realize just how much her Father had protected herself and Thomas from the reality of ruling a nation."

    old "Sarah threw off her blankets, got out of bed and walked to her closet."
    new "Sarah threw off her blankets, got out of bed and walked to her closet."

    old "She began pulling out dresses, one by one, seeing what would send the right message at today's council meeting."
    new "She began pulling out dresses, one by one, seeing what would send the right message at today's council meeting."

    old "Sarah settled on one that she believed would make the right impression. One that would ensure the men at the council would take her serious."
    new "Sarah settled on one that she believed would make the right impression. One that would ensure the men at the council would take her serious."

    old "She put on her clothes and set out for the council room."
    new "She put on her clothes and set out for the council room."

    old "Sarah awakes in her bed. Light is filtering in through the window."
    new "Sarah awakes in her bed. Light is filtering in through the window."

    old "She looks across her bedroom. Much like the rest of the castle, it had felt strangely empty since her father had passed."
    new "She looks across her bedroom. Much like the rest of the castle, it had felt strangely empty since her father had passed."

    old "She felt alone, in ways she had never felt alone before."
    new "She felt alone, in ways she had never felt alone before."

    old "She recalled Kate's visit from the night before. She hadn't meant to sound as harsh as she did, but the words had just slipped out."
    new "She recalled Kate's visit from the night before. She hadn't meant to sound as harsh as she did, but the words had just slipped out."

    old "Sarah considered apologizing to her friend next time she saw her."
    new "Sarah considered apologizing to her friend next time she saw her."

    old "She shook her head, trying to clear her thoughts. Sarah knew that she was too busy to be worrying herself over every sleight."
    new "She shook her head, trying to clear her thoughts. Sarah knew that she was too busy to be worrying herself over every sleight."

    old "There was work to be done. Every day, more and more people came to her and Thomas, the requests were endless."
    new "There was work to be done. Every day, more and more people came to her and Thomas, the requests were endless."

    old "Sarah settled on one that she believed would make the right impression. One that would ensure the people at the council would take her serious."
    new "Sarah settled on one that she believed would make the right impression. One that would ensure the people at the council would take her serious."

    old "Sarah arrived at the council room."
    new "Sarah arrived at the council room."

    old "The ceilings on the room were low, and there were no windows anywhere. Other than the central table, the room was sparse."
    new "The ceilings on the room were low, and there were no windows anywhere. Other than the central table, the room was sparse."

    old "It had been designed with secrecy in mind, giving no space for anyone to hide, but it had unintentionally gave the room a claustrophobic feeling."
    new "It had been designed with secrecy in mind, giving no space for anyone to hide, but it had unintentionally gave the room a claustrophobic feeling."

    old "Some people had nicknamed the room, the crypt. Standing in the room now, Sarah understood what they meant."
    new "Some people had nicknamed the room, the crypt. Standing in the room now, Sarah understood what they meant."

    old "She saw that Thomas had arrived before her."
    new "She saw that Thomas had arrived before her."

    old "He did not greet her as she approached, staring off into the distance, lost in thought."
    new "He did not greet her as she approached, staring off into the distance, lost in thought."

    old "Ready for the meeting?"
    new "Ready for the meeting?"

    old "Thomas jolted, quickly sitting upright, before realizing it was his sister."
    new "Thomas jolted, quickly sitting upright, before realizing it was his sister."

    old "Ooh, I didn't hear you come in."
    new "Ooh, I didn't hear you come in."

    old "Sarah sat down in the chair next to her brother."
    new "Sarah sat down in the chair next to her brother."

    old "She saw the same dark rings around his eyes as from the day before."
    new "She saw the same dark rings around his eyes as from the day before."

    old "She placed her hand on his arm."
    new "She placed her hand on his arm."

    old "Thomas, did you manage to get any sleep last night?"
    new "Thomas, did you manage to get any sleep last night?"

    old "Thomas stared past her, vacantly. He softly shook his head."
    new "Thomas stared past her, vacantly. He softly shook his head."

    old "I just...I couldnt..."
    new "I just...I couldnt..."

    old "He kept pausing between his words, as if he had to keep remembering the words."
    new "He kept pausing between his words, as if he had to keep remembering the words."

    old "I lie in bed, and I just stare up at the ceiling. I walk around the castle at night. I sat out in the courtyard."
    new "I lie in bed, and I just stare up at the ceiling. I walk around the castle at night. I sat out in the courtyard."

    old "But the sleep doesn't come to me. No matter what I do."
    new "But the sleep doesn't come to me. No matter what I do."

    old "Thomas put his head in his hands."
    new "Thomas put his head in his hands."

    old "I keep thinking about Dad. And when I'm not thinking about him, I think about all of this..."
    new "I keep thinking about Dad. And when I'm not thinking about him, I think about all of this..."

    old "He motions around the table."
    new "He motions around the table."

    old "People come up to me. They keep asking me endless questions, expecting me to have the answer."
    new "People come up to me. They keep asking me endless questions, expecting me to have the answer."

    old "Thomas turned to his sister."
    new "Thomas turned to his sister."

    old "I don't have them Sarah. They're asking me for solutions to problems I didn't even know we had."
    new "I don't have them Sarah. They're asking me for solutions to problems I didn't even know we had."

    old "And the advisors, they bring me stacks of reports. I can't even read half of them before they bring me more."
    new "And the advisors, they bring me stacks of reports. I can't even read half of them before they bring me more."

    old "Sarah listened to her brother share his troubles. She knew how hard everything weighed on Thomas."
    new "Sarah listened to her brother share his troubles. She knew how hard everything weighed on Thomas."

    old "Her brother was a good person. He blamed himself for every shortcoming, yet also pushed himself to do more."
    new "Her brother was a good person. He blamed himself for every shortcoming, yet also pushed himself to do more."

    old "That was his curse, Sarah thought. If her brother had simply not cared, or been lazier, he wouldn't have demanded so much from himself. He wouldn't push himself this hard."
    new "That was his curse, Sarah thought. If her brother had simply not cared, or been lazier, he wouldn't have demanded so much from himself. He wouldn't push himself this hard."

    old "Perhaps, Thomas, I can help you?"
    new "Perhaps, Thomas, I can help you?"

    old "How?"
    new "How?"

    old "We could divide some of the reports. You read half, and I read the other half. Then we can inform each other of what is important. Share the burden."
    new "We could divide some of the reports. You read half, and I read the other half. Then we can inform each other of what is important. Share the burden."

    old "Thomas listened intently, nodding along."
    new "Thomas listened intently, nodding along."

    old "You're right. But...would you do that for me, Sarah? I mean, I will be king. This should be my burden."
    new "You're right. But...would you do that for me, Sarah? I mean, I will be king. This should be my burden."

    old "Thomas, when did I ever let you carry your burdens alone?"
    new "Thomas, when did I ever let you carry your burdens alone?"

    old "Thomas smiled."
    new "Thomas smiled."

    old "Never."
    new "Never."

    old "That's right. It's going to be just as before, when I would read father's books, and tell you the important parts. Working together, as a brother and sister should."
    new "That's right. It's going to be just as before, when I would read father's books, and tell you the important parts. Working together, as a brother and sister should."

    old "I would like that. Thank you Sarah."
    new "I would like that. Thank you Sarah."

    old "Sarah patted her brother on the shoulder."
    new "Sarah patted her brother on the shoulder."

    old "A good king needs good advisors, and do you know anyone smarter than me?"
    new "A good king needs good advisors, and do you know anyone smarter than me?"

    old "Sarah laughed."
    new "Sarah laughed."

    old "Thomas simply squeezed her hands, and repeated himself."
    new "Thomas simply squeezed her hands, and repeated himself."

    old "Thank you."
    new "Thank you."

    old "Sarah and Thomas spent some time chatting, before the door to the council room finally swung open. The other members of the council entered the room."
    new "Sarah and Thomas spent some time chatting, before the door to the council room finally swung open. The other members of the council entered the room."

    old "Marching at the front of everyone else was High General Barion, followed closely by the Spymaster Kravel. Walking furthest behind was Lady Carolyn, master of the royal accounts."
    new "Marching at the front of everyone else was High General Barion, followed closely by the Spymaster Kravel. Walking furthest behind was Lady Carolyn, master of the royal accounts."

    old "Each member bowed, first to Thomas, then to Sarah, before taking their place at the table."
    new "Each member bowed, first to Thomas, then to Sarah, before taking their place at the table."

    old "General Barion was the longest sitting member of the council. He had served in every conflict Rosanna had fought under King Orwell."
    new "General Barion was the longest sitting member of the council. He had served in every conflict Rosanna had fought under King Orwell."

    old "He was an accomplished general, and most soldiers loved him for having fought side-by-side with them on the battlefield. Some generals in Rosanna's army had not so much as seen a battle."
    new "He was an accomplished general, and most soldiers loved him for having fought side-by-side with them on the battlefield. Some generals in Rosanna's army had not so much as seen a battle."

    old "Spymaster Kravel had been on the council for a little over a decade. He had replaced the old spymaster who had plotted to sabotage king Orwell's peace negotiations with Rosanna's neighbor, Normandi."
    new "Spymaster Kravel had been on the council for a little over a decade. He had replaced the old spymaster who had plotted to sabotage king Orwell's peace negotiations with Rosanna's neighbor, Normandi."

    old "Kravel had informed King Orwell of the plot, and for his loyalty and talents, received his promotion."
    new "Kravel had informed King Orwell of the plot, and for his loyalty and talents, received his promotion."

    old "Ever since he had served competently, overseeing both the internal security of Rosanna and managing its foreign affairs."
    new "Ever since he had served competently, overseeing both the internal security of Rosanna and managing its foreign affairs."

    old "Spymasters were hard to trust, by the nature of their work, but as far as possible, Kravel had proven reliable and loyal. It was the best one could hope from a spymaster."
    new "Spymasters were hard to trust, by the nature of their work, but as far as possible, Kravel had proven reliable and loyal. It was the best one could hope from a spymaster."

    old "Lastly was Lady Carolyn. As master of the royal accounts, she oversaw the economy of Rosanna."
    new "Lastly was Lady Carolyn. As master of the royal accounts, she oversaw the economy of Rosanna."

    old "Managing everything from the tax laws to the foreign trade agreements, it was a position as important as any other on the council."
    new "Managing everything from the tax laws to the foreign trade agreements, it was a position as important as any other on the council."

    old "In fact, some reasoned, in times of peace, it was likely the most important position. Masters of the accounts had been known to bring financial ruin to a family with the stroke of a pen."
    new "In fact, some reasoned, in times of peace, it was likely the most important position. Masters of the accounts had been known to bring financial ruin to a family with the stroke of a pen."

    old "After everyone had taken their seat, a silence lingered in the air."
    new "After everyone had taken their seat, a silence lingered in the air."

    old "Sarah kicked Thomas under the table."
    new "Sarah kicked Thomas under the table."

    old "Ouch! AAH, uhm, yes, thank you for attending this meeting."
    new "Ouch! AAH, uhm, yes, thank you for attending this meeting."

    old "Barion was the first to speak."
    new "Barion was the first to speak."

    old "Of course, my liege."
    new "Of course, my liege."

    old "The others silently bowed in acknowledgement."
    new "The others silently bowed in acknowledgement."

    old "Thomas cleared his throat and began to speak more forcefully."
    new "Thomas cleared his throat and began to speak more forcefully."

    old "This is the first meeting of the council since my father's death."
    new "This is the first meeting of the council since my father's death."

    old "There is a lot that needs to be done. I expect from each of you, the loyalty that you showed my father."
    new "There is a lot that needs to be done. I expect from each of you, the loyalty that you showed my father."

    old "This time, it was Lady Carolyn who spoke."
    new "This time, it was Lady Carolyn who spoke."

    old "Prince Thomas, let me assure you, it was my greatest pleasure to serve your father, and I pray that I may only be so fortunate as you honor him by serving you."
    new "Prince Thomas, let me assure you, it was my greatest pleasure to serve your father, and I pray that I may only be so fortunate as you honor him by serving you."

    old "Sarah noticed how Carolyn carried herself. She exuded an air of supreme confidence in herself. As if there was no doubt that she belonged on the council."
    new "Sarah noticed how Carolyn carried herself. She exuded an air of supreme confidence in herself. As if there was no doubt that she belonged on the council."

    old "She occupied a function not often filled by women, but if it was a doubt she harbored you would never have known it from how she carried herself."
    new "She occupied a function not often filled by women, but if it was a doubt she harbored you would never have known it from how she carried herself."

    old "Good, I'm glad to hear that."
    new "Good, I'm glad to hear that."

    old "Thomas turned to the spymaster."
    new "Thomas turned to the spymaster."

    old "Now, Kravel, as the first item for this meeting, I want to know if you have any ideas on the murder of my father."
    new "Now, Kravel, as the first item for this meeting, I want to know if you have any ideas on the murder of my father."

    old "It was silent for a while, the word murder, seemingly dominating the room."
    new "It was silent for a while, the word murder, seemingly dominating the room."

    old "So far, my liege, I fear that we do not know very much at all."
    new "So far, my liege, I fear that we do not know very much at all."

    old "It has not been the first time that there was a plot against your father, but the odd thing is, we always picked up rumors whenever there were plans for an assassination."
    new "It has not been the first time that there was a plot against your father, but the odd thing is, we always picked up rumors whenever there were plans for an assassination."

    old "Kravel began to tap his fingers on the table, as if trying to summon a memory."
    new "Kravel began to tap his fingers on the table, as if trying to summon a memory."

    old "This time, however, I must confess, I have heard not so much as a whisper."
    new "This time, however, I must confess, I have heard not so much as a whisper."

    old "Additionally, we would usually expect to see an assassination followed by some kind of follow up. A foreign enemy invading, plotters trying to seize the capital."
    new "Additionally, we would usually expect to see an assassination followed by some kind of follow up. A foreign enemy invading, plotters trying to seize the capital."

    old "Kravel waited for a moment."
    new "Kravel waited for a moment."

    old "And yet, we see nothing. No force inside or outside the kingdom has sought to seize on this moment. Our alliances remain strong. Only kind words have made their way here."
    new "And yet, we see nothing. No force inside or outside the kingdom has sought to seize on this moment. Our alliances remain strong. Only kind words have made their way here."

    old "At the very least, I believe it safe to conclude that there is no larger plot being carried out."
    new "At the very least, I believe it safe to conclude that there is no larger plot being carried out."

    old "Barion scoffed."
    new "Barion scoffed."

    old "And how could you be so certain? You didn't see this attack coming. Maybe you're missing the next."
    new "And how could you be so certain? You didn't see this attack coming. Maybe you're missing the next."

    old "Kravel looked annoyed."
    new "Kravel looked annoyed."

    old "One can miss a single assassin in the dead of night, but I would notice an army on the move. We see nothing of the kind."
    new "One can miss a single assassin in the dead of night, but I would notice an army on the move. We see nothing of the kind."

    old "What then of Hassar?"
    new "What then of Hassar?"

    old "Kravel raised up his hand, as if to wave away the subject."
    new "Kravel raised up his hand, as if to wave away the subject."

    old "That is a different topic."
    new "That is a different topic."

    old "Thomas leaned in."
    new "Thomas leaned in."

    old "Hassar?"
    new "Hassar?"

    old "He is a barbarian, little more, an upstart really. He hails from the eastern desert."
    new "He is a barbarian, little more, an upstart really. He hails from the eastern desert."

    old "Barion interupted."
    new "Barion interupted."

    old "He is more than that, Prince Thomas, he has conquered the desert tribes and forged them into a single force."
    new "He is more than that, Prince Thomas, he has conquered the desert tribes and forged them into a single force."

    old "This time, Kravel interrupted."
    new "This time, Kravel interrupted."

    old "Those are the rumors, my lord. We do not yet have enough evidence to suggest that he has truly united them."
    new "Those are the rumors, my lord. We do not yet have enough evidence to suggest that he has truly united them."

    old "High General Barion is an army man, so he loves to imagine every enemy an existential threat to our nation. It makes him feel needed."
    new "High General Barion is an army man, so he loves to imagine every enemy an existential threat to our nation. It makes him feel needed."

    old "Thomas considered what he was hearing."
    new "Thomas considered what he was hearing."

    old "He leaned towards his sister and whispered."
    new "He leaned towards his sister and whispered."

    old "What do you think, Sarah?"
    new "What do you think, Sarah?"

    old "He could be a serious threat."
    new "He could be a serious threat."

    old "He could be a serious threat. We should send scouts or spies to investigate."
    new "He could be a serious threat. We should send scouts or spies to investigate."

    old "Let's not get carried away by mere rumors."
    new "Let's not get carried away by mere rumors."

    old "The eastern tribes like to boast. I think it's too soon to waste real resources chasing some phantom."
    new "The eastern tribes like to boast. I think it's too soon to waste real resources chasing some phantom."

    old "We'll need to know if this man, Hassar, is a real threat, or just a boasting savage."
    new "We'll need to know if this man, Hassar, is a real threat, or just a boasting savage."

    old "Spymaster, I want you to send scouts to the eastern desert. See what they report back to us."
    new "Spymaster, I want you to send scouts to the eastern desert. See what they report back to us."

    old "Thomas continued."
    new "Thomas continued."

    old "Also, High General Barion, begin by moving some units to our eastern provinces, just in case."
    new "Also, High General Barion, begin by moving some units to our eastern provinces, just in case."

    old "Yes, my lord."
    new "Yes, my lord."

    old "I agree with my sister. Right now, we can't be moving army units across the country, just because some farmers think they saw something."
    new "I agree with my sister. Right now, we can't be moving army units across the country, just because some farmers think they saw something."

    old "Thomas seemed to grow more at ease in his role."
    new "Thomas seemed to grow more at ease in his role."

    old "That settles the matter of Hassar and the desert tribes. What is left on the agenda for today?"
    new "That settles the matter of Hassar and the desert tribes. What is left on the agenda for today?"

    old "Lady Carolyn leaned forward."
    new "Lady Carolyn leaned forward."

    old "My prince, there is the matter of your coronation."
    new "My prince, there is the matter of your coronation."

    old "Sarah knew this was on the agenda. The event itself was a formality, but she worried about how Thomas would handle such an event."
    new "Sarah knew this was on the agenda. The event itself was a formality, but she worried about how Thomas would handle such an event."

    old "Her brother didn't like to be the center of attention, but on a day like that, there would be no going around it."
    new "Her brother didn't like to be the center of attention, but on a day like that, there would be no going around it."

    old "She saw Thomas fidget in his seat."
    new "She saw Thomas fidget in his seat."

    old "Aah, yes, well said Lady Carolyn. My coronation..."
    new "Aah, yes, well said Lady Carolyn. My coronation..."

    old "We need to decide on the...practicalities. Who to invite, the meals, the city's festivities. A lot to consider."
    new "We need to decide on the...practicalities. Who to invite, the meals, the city's festivities. A lot to consider."

    old "Sarah could see Thomas furrow his brow, simply imagining the extravagant event."
    new "Sarah could see Thomas furrow his brow, simply imagining the extravagant event."

    old "Is such a large event really neccesary?"
    new "Is such a large event really neccesary?"

    old "Well, my prince, we need to consider appearances. Events like this only come along very rarely."
    new "Well, my prince, we need to consider appearances. Events like this only come along very rarely."

    old "The nobility will expect something impressive. A show of our nation's prosperity."
    new "The nobility will expect something impressive. A show of our nation's prosperity."

    old "They might consider a small coronation to be a sign of weakness."
    new "They might consider a small coronation to be a sign of weakness."

    old "Thomas leaned to Sarah again."
    new "Thomas leaned to Sarah again."

    old "What do you think we should do?"
